    {
      "type": "contrast_example",
      "content": "Notice the difference: In the first two poems, we used <span class='highlight'>なり (nari)</span> to end the sentence. In this poem, we use <span class='highlight'>なる (naru)</span>. Why? Because it is modifying the noun 'washi' (eagle/peak). 'Sayaka-naru washi' = 'The peak that is clear'. This is the 'Attributive Form' (Rentaikei). In Chinese, this is like using '...的' to describe a noun (清澈的...)."
    },
